matipNumUsers.name: matipNumUsers
matipNumUsers.description: Number of users in the table.

matipUserTable.name: matipUserTable
matipUserTable.description: A list of line table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of matipNumUsers.

matipUserEntry.name: matipUserEntry
matipUserEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular MATIP user.

matipUserHLD.name: matipUserHLD
matipUserHLD.description: The HLD associated with this device.

matipUserA1.name: matipUserA1
matipUserA1.description: The A1 associated with this device.

matipUserA2.name: matipUserA2
matipUserA2.description: The A2 associated with this device.

matipUserSessionRef.name: matipUserSessionRef
matipUserSessionRef.description: The MATIP session identifier (i.e. the interface index of the associated MATIP session). At configuration time, if the value is zero, then session has not been pre-allocated; otherwise, this value signifies the configured session to use.

matipUserCoding.name: matipUserCoding
matipUserCoding.description: Defines the coding or data that is associated with this entry: paddedbaudot: 5 bits ipars: 6 bits ascii: 7 bits ebcdic: 8 bits

matipUserPresentationMode.name: matipUserPresentationMode
matipUserPresentationMode.description: The type of presentation: p1024b p1024c sna3270 (not currently supported)

matipUserQueueThresholdHi.name: matipUserQueueThresholdHi
matipUserQueueThresholdHi.description: Count of messages queued to the MATIP user before flow control is initiated by 'pushing back' on the MATIP session stream.

matipUserQueueThresholdLow.name: matipUserQueueThresholdLow
matipUserQueueThresholdLow.description: Count of messages queued to the MATIP user before re-enabling on the MATIP session stream.

matipUserStateTime.name: matipUserStateTime
matipUserStateTime.description: The amount of time (in hundredths of a second) since this user entered the current state.

matipUserStatus.name: matipUserStatus
matipUserStatus.description: Connect State of the MATIP User

matipUserMsgsIn.name: matipUserMsgsIn
matipUserMsgsIn.description: The total number of messages from the Type A device.

matipUserMsgsOut.name: matipUserMsgsOut
matipUserMsgsOut.description: The total number of messages sent to the Type A device.

matipUserCharIn.name: matipUserCharIn
matipUserCharIn.description: The total number of characters from the Type A device.

matipUserCharOut.name: matipUserCharOut
matipUserCharOut.description: The total number of characters sent to the Type A device.

matipUserDisconnects.name: matipUserDisconnects
matipUserDisconnects.description: The total number of MATIP User disconnects.

matipUserTrapReason.name: matipUserTrapReason
matipUserTrapReason.description: The reason that the matipUserStateChange trap was generated: up - when the MATIP User enters 'connected' state. down - when the MATIP User enters 'disconnected' state.

matipUserStateChangeTrapEnable.name: matipUserStateChangeTrapEnable
matipUserStateChangeTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether matipUserStateChange traps should be generated for this interface. disabled - do not generate a trap enabled - generate trap when a user enters either the connected or disconnected state. partial - same as 'enabled' except only for those MATIP sessions initiated by this end.

matipUserStateChange.name: matipUserStateChange
matipUserStateChange.description: This trap signifies that one of the users has changed state to/from connected/disconnected as given by matipUserTrapReason.

matipSessionEntry.name: matipSessionEntry
matipSessionEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular MATIP session.

matipSessionIndex.name: matipSessionIndex
matipSessionIndex.description: The identifier that can be used to locate this session.

matipSessionClientServer.name: matipSessionClientServer
matipSessionClientServer.description: Flag defining the Client/Server nature of the product. 'both' is not supported by TIGER because 'client' serves as both client and server.

matipSessionMuxMode.name: matipSessionMuxMode
matipSessionMuxMode.description: Multiplexor Mode for this session defined as follows: HLD/A1/A2: 4 Byte ASCU definition A1/A2: 2 Byte ASCU definition Single: No multiplexing.

matipSessionPresentationMode.name: matipSessionPresentationMode
matipSessionPresentationMode.description: The type of presentation: p1024b p1024c sna3270 (not currently supported)

matipSessionCoding.name: matipSessionCoding
matipSessionCoding.description: Defines the coding or data that is associated with this entry: paddedbaudot: 5 bits, ipars: 6 bits, ascii: 7 bits, ebcdic: 8 bits

matipSessionRestartTimer.name: matipSessionRestartTimer
matipSessionRestartTimer.description: The number of seconds that will be waited before the MATIP session will be restarted. A value of zero indicates that timing will not occur. The session restart timer is only used when matipSessionClientServer is set to 'client' and matipSessionDialOnDemand is 'disabled'.

matipSessionDialOnDemand.name: matipSessionDialOnDemand
matipSessionDialOnDemand.description: When dial on demand is enabled, the TCP session will only be started upon received data from the MATIP user.

matipSessionActivityTimer.name: matipSessionActivityTimer
matipSessionActivityTimer.description: The number of seconds of inactivity before the TCP session will be disconnected.

matipSessionQueueThresholdHi.name: matipSessionQueueThresholdHi
matipSessionQueueThresholdHi.description: The queueing limit for traffic being sent to the AUTIF module. When this is reached, the software will push back against the MATIP users.

matipSessionQueueThresholdLow.name: matipSessionQueueThresholdLow
matipSessionQueueThresholdLow.description: The level at which the user queues will be re-enabled.

matipSessionConnectTime.name: matipSessionConnectTime
matipSessionConnectTime.description: The amount of time (in hundredths of a second) since this transport connection last entered the 'connected' state. A value of zero means this transport connection has never been established.

matipSessionStatus.name: matipSessionStatus
matipSessionStatus.description: The state of this transport connection: 'sessionDown' - when this MATIP session is created by the configuration, or when the TCP connection fails. 'sessionActivated' - when the MATIP state machine has sent an SO command and is waiting for an OC response. 'sessionConnected' - when the MATIP session layer can begin Data Transfer.

matipSessionDisconnects.name: matipSessionDisconnects
matipSessionDisconnects.description: The Total number of MATIP session Disconnects.

matipSessionSOSent.name: matipSessionSOSent
matipSessionSOSent.description: The count of SO Commands sent.

matipSessionSOReceived.name: matipSessionSOReceived
matipSessionSOReceived.description: The count of SO Commands received.

matipSessionOCSent.name: matipSessionOCSent
matipSessionOCSent.description: The count of OC Commands sent.

matipSessionOCReceived.name: matipSessionOCReceived
matipSessionOCReceived.description: The count of OC Commands received.

matipSessionSCSent.name: matipSessionSCSent
matipSessionSCSent.description: The count of SC Commands sent.

matipSessionSCReceived.name: matipSessionSCReceived
matipSessionSCReceived.description: The count of SC Commands received.

matipSessionDataSent.name: matipSessionDataSent
matipSessionDataSent.description: The count of data packets sent.

matipSessionDataReceived.name: matipSessionDataReceived
matipSessionDataReceived.description: The count of data packets received.

matipSessionStateChangeTrapEnable.name: matipSessionStateChangeTrapEnable
matipSessionStateChangeTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether matipSessionStateChange traps should be generated for this interface. disabled - do not generate a trap enabled - generate trap when a session enters either the connected or disconnected state. or when any 'partner reject' occurs. partial - same as 'enabled' except only when the session is closed with busy.

matipSessionTrapReason.name: matipSessionTrapReason
matipSessionTrapReason.description: The reason that the matipSessionStateChange trap was generated: up - when the session enters 'connected' state. down - when the session enters 'disconnected' state.

matipSessionStateChange.name: matipSessionStateChange
matipSessionStateChange.description: This trap signifies that one of the sessions has changed state to/from connected/disconnected as given by matipSessionTrapReason.
